help:
    npm help
    npm help <commandname>
updates npm:
    npm install npm -g
initialixze npm:
    npm init
npm login:
    npm whoami
    npm adduser
setting git:
    git init
start a project:
    npm init --scope=<username>
install a dependency:
    npm install <modulename> (example @linclark/pkg)
while installing, etc also update the package.json:
    npm install <modulename> --save
list all dependencies
    npm ls
testing:
    <package.json> - "test": "node <test-file>.js"
    npm test
publish:
    npm publish
verion number:
    Semantic Version - http://semver.org
    1.2.3
    ^ ^ ^
    | | `-- Patch version. Update for every change.
    | `---- Minor version. Update for API additions.
    `------ Major version. Update for breaking API changes.
npm version updating:
    npm version
    manually in package.json (change version number before updating)
changing distibrution tag:
    npm dist-tag add pkg@1.0.1 beta
    npm dist-tag rm pkg@1.0.1
    default is latest, which always point to some version or other
    always latest version is downloaded, so change tag latest as needed
list outdated packages:
    npm outdated
update to latest(tag):
    npm update
uninstall or remove:
    npm rm --save
    npm uninstall --save
    --save makes sure that even after the dep has been removed, we still
    don't depend on it by removing it from package.json
view https://www.npmjs.com/ for more.